        public static java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> qtyAnimalToSell(java.util.ArrayList<Animal> animals,
                                                                                    AnimalType animalType,
                                                                                    AnimalMinWeight animalMinWeight)
        This method calc how many animals are ready to sell based on the minimum weight needed for each animal and based on the type of the animal.
        Parameters:
        animals - is an ArrayList of animal. This ArrayList must have all the animals we want to verify.
        animalType - is an AnimalType we want to search within the ArrayList.
        animalMinWeight - is an AnimalMinWeight with the value of the minimum weight we should consider.
        Returns:
        HashMap is a pair value list with the result.

      • qtyAllAnimalsToSell

        public static java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> qtyAllAnimalsToSell(java.util.ArrayList<Animal> animals)
        This method calc how many animals are ready to sell based on the minimum weight needed for each animal and based on the type of the animal. Different from the method above, this method count all the animals ready to sell whereas the first method make the calc based on only one type of animal.
        Parameters:
        animals - is an ArrayList of animal. This ArrayList must have all the animals we want to verify.
        Returns:
        HashMap is a pair value list with the result.
